<div class="argument-item">
	<h4 id="eating-animals-is-necessary">
		Eating animals is necessary</h4>
	<p>Eating animals is not necessary. There are millions of vegans across the globe and from all paths of life
		that lead perfectly healthy lives. In fact, the <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27886704/" target="_blank"
			rel="noreferrer noopener">Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics</a>, the United States’ <a
			href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_of_Nutrition_and_Dietetics" target="_blank"
			rel="noreferrer noopener">largest organisation of food and nutrition professionals</a>, states the
		following:</p>
	<blockquote>“It is the position of the Academy of Nutrition and
		Dietetics that appropriately planned vegetarian, including <strong>vegan, diets
			are healthful, nutritionally adequate and may provide health benefits
			for the prevention and treatment of certain diseases.</strong> These diets are
		appropriate for all stages of the life cycle, including pregnancy,
		lactation, infancy, childhood, adolescence, older adulthood and for
		athletes. Plant-based diets are more environmentally sustainable than
		diets rich in animal products because they use fewer natural resources
		and are associated with much less environmental damage. Vegetarians and
		vegans are at reduced risk of certain health conditions, including
		ischemic heart disease, type 2 diabetes, hypertension, certain types of
		cancer, and obesity.”</blockquote>
	<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4081456/" target="_blank"
			rel="noreferrer noopener">largest study ever on vegan nutrient profiles</a> found:</p>
	<blockquote>“In strict vegetarians, low dietary intakes of vitamin B12
		and D, calcium, and omega-3 fatty acids, in addition to iron and zinc,
		have often been of concern <sup><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4081456/#R25" target="_blank"
				rel="noreferrer noopener">25</a></sup>. In the present study, mean intakes of these
		nutrients were above minimum requirements <sup><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4081456/#R26"
				target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">26</a></sup> in strict vegetarians.”</blockquote>
	<p>In a modern environment where one is not living in a state of survival there is quite simply <a
			href="https://viva.org.uk/animals/number-animals-killed/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">no
			need to exploit and slaughter billions of sentient beings</a>. All necessary nutrients can be found in a
		healthy vegan diet.</p>
