<div class="argument-item">
	<h4 id="eating-animals-is-natural">
		Eating animals is natural</h4>
	<p>It doesn’t matter if it’s natural, because this doesn’t imply eating meat is ethical or good. This is known
		as an “<a href="https://yourlogicalfallacyis.com/appeal-to-nature" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">appeal
			to nature fallacy</a>”. We don’t do things solely because they’re
		natural. We use
		planes, cars, buildings, clothing, cutlery, cups, glasses, and an array
		of things that are not natural. There are other natural things we avoid,
		such as killing members of our own species and forcibly impregnating
		females, because nature is a violent place. Some diseases and health
		problems are natural, but we do whatever we can to get cured.</p>
	<p>Our civilisation is largely focused on reducing suffering
		rather than in staying aligned with nature. In many cases, we strive to
		avoid the dangers of nature. We should do what’s ethical, not what’s
		natural. Killing animals when we don’t need to is unethical, period.</p>
