<div class="argument-item">
	<h4 id="humans-are-superior-to-animals">
		Humans are superior to animals</h4>
	<p>In some ways, yes we are superior in many aspects.</p>
	<blockquote>I don't hold animals superior or even equal to humans. The whole case for behaving decently to
		animals rests on the fact that we are the superior species. We are the species uniquely capable of
		imagination, rationality and moral choice – and that is precisely why we are under the obligation to
		recognise and respect the rights of animals.<br /><br />— Brigid Brophy</blockquote>
	<p>However, we’re not superior
		in our ability to fly or see in the dark, to exist under water or to navigate naturally by magnetic fields.
		It could be argued that some
		humans are superior to other humans in certain areas. Some humans are
		smarter, faster, stronger, better looking and so on. By this logic, the
		“superior” humans could in theory abuse the “inferior” ones.</p>
	<p>Superiority doesn’t grant us a right to abuse other sentient
		beings. In fact, this line of thinking is what justified many atrocities
		in the past, like The Holocaust, black segregation, disenfranchisement
		of women, and so on. Of course, nobody wants animals to have the same
		rights as humans, like the right to vote, because this doesn’t make
		sense. What does make sense, however, is to grant them the right to life
		because their sentience means they have an interest to live, just like
		us.</p>
