<div class="argument-item">
	<h4 id="animals-are-humanely-slaughtered">
		Animals are humanely slaughtered</h4>
	<p>We can, in theory (and not at the large scale required to feed 8 billion humans), kill an animal without
		any pain. However, this does not make the act of killing morally acceptable. Killing animals, thus depriving
		them of their right to life, for selfish desires like your appetite, is wrong.</p>
	<p>The <a href="https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/humane" target="_blank"
			rel="noreferrer noopener">definition of the word “humane”</a> is:</p>
	<blockquote>“Having or showing compassion or benevolence”.</blockquote>
	<p>Synonyms include “compassionate”, “kind” and “considerate”. Therefore, “humane” and “shooting animals”, are
		not compatible.</p>
	<p>No truly compassionate person capable of empathy would want to take the lives away from animals for
		something as trivial as a sandwich filling.</p>
